  "prompt": "My friends rented an Airbnb and the host charged them 5x the security deposit after we checked out. Is it smart to contest this?",
  "response": "Yes, it's usually smart to contest an unusually large security deposit charge. Here are some steps:\n\n1. Review the original listing and rental agreement carefully\n2. Take photos documenting the condition of the property when you left\n3. Get copies of the cleaning/damage reports from the host\n4. Contact Airbnb customer support and explain the situation\n5. Provide evidence that the charges seem excessive\n6. Request a review of the charges\n7. If Airbnb doesn't help, you may be able to dispute the charge with your credit card\n\nThe key is having documentation and being able to show the charges are unreasonable.",
